**Story**  

Once upon a time, there lived a monkey resided on a berry tree full of berries that was 
on the banks of the river. In the same forest, there lived a crocodile with his wife. One 
day the crocodile came to the banks of the river and rested under the tree. The kind hearted
offered him some fruits. The crocodile came back the next day for more fruits as he loved those juicy
Berries. As the days passed by, the monkey and crocodile became very good friends.
One day the monkey sent some fruits as an act of kindness for the Crocodile's wife. The Crocodile's
wife ate the fruits and love them but was jealous and she didn't like her husband to spend most 
his time with the monkey. She told her husband,"If the fruits are so delicious and juicy, I woner how
tasty and sweet the monkey's heart would be. Get me the heart of monkey either by Hook or Crook."
The crocodile was not willing to kill his very good friend but he had no choice and he had to keep hiswife's wish.
